summary: 05/05/1993: Chinese United Nations Transitional Authority in Cambodia (UNTAC) forces were attacked in Kompong Thom, Cambodia. Two buildings were damaged, but there were no casualties. The Khmer Rouge, the suspected perpetrators of the attack, denied involvement, instead blaming the attack on the Vietnamese.
target1: United Nations Transitional  Authority in Cambodia Forces
propcomment: Two buildings were damaged in the attack.
